bzh.plealog.bioinfo.api.data.feature

Class FPosition

  • java.lang.Object
    • bzh.plealog.bioinfo.api.data.feature.FPosition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class FPosition
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Defines a position. This class can model the three kind of positions defined in the official NCBI/EBI/DDBJ Feature Table specification document: unique position, between bases position and in range position.

    Note: FPosition alone has no real meaning. They have to be combined by pair to form a FRange which represents a real feature location. Among others, this is the reason why dbXref is assigned to a FRange.
    Author:
    Patrick G. Durand

        Constructs a range position, with optionally fuzzy start and end.
        Parameters:
        fs - pass in true to specify spanning start
        fe - pass in true to specify a spanning end
        s - the start of the position. Value is one-based.
        e - the end of the position. Value is one-based.
        t - the type of the position. Use one of the constants BETWEEN_BASES, IN_RANGE or UNIQUE defined in this class.
